.TH VINMAIL 1 "2026" "vinmail 1.1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
vinmail \- interactive terminal mail client for msmtp with multi-account and GPG support

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vinmail

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vinmail
is a lightweight, Bash-based terminal mail client built on top of msmtp.
It provides an interactive text-based interface for managing multiple
email accounts and composing and sending mail directly from the terminal.

Navigation is performed using arrow keys or j/k, Enter to select, and q to cancel.

.SH MENU OPTIONS
.TP
.B Switch active account
Set the active account by copying its configuration to ~/.msmtprc.

.TP
.B Add account
Launch a guided setup wizard. Leaving any prompt empty aborts the process.

.TP
.B Edit / Rename / Test
Modify account settings, update credentials, rename aliases, view configuration,
or test SMTP connectivity.

.TP
.B Delete account
Remove an account and its credentials. Requires typing 'yes' to confirm.

.TP
.B Compose & send mail
Open the full compose interface where To, Cc, Bcc, and Subject can be edited at any time.
The message body is written in $EDITOR. Supports file attachments and optional GPG signing.

.TP
.B Status
Display a table of all configured accounts along with their encryption status.

.SH COMPOSE KEYS
.TP
.B t
Edit recipient (To)

.TP
.B c
Edit Cc

.TP
.B b
Edit Bcc

.TP
.B s
Edit Subject

.TP
.B e
Open message body in $EDITOR

.TP
.B a
Manage attachments (add or remove files)

.TP
.B g
Toggle GPG signing and select signing key

.TP
.B y
Send message (with preview confirmation)

.TP
.B q
Discard draft and exit compose mode

.SH AUTHOR
Written by VintellX.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR msmtp (1),
.BR gpg (1)
